{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "[Article Title - 110 characters max]",
  "description": "[Brief description of article content - 150 characters]",
  "image": {
    "@type": "ImageObject",
    "url": "[https://yourdomain.com/images/article-image.jpg]",
    "width": 1200,
    "height": 630,
    "caption": "[Image description]"
  },
  "datePublished": "[2025-01-15T10:00:00Z]",
  "dateModified": "[2025-11-11T14:30:00Z]",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "[Dr. Full Name]",
    "honorificPrefix": "[Dr.]",
    "honorificSuffix": "[MD, PhD]",
    "url": "[https://yourdomain.com/about/author-name]",
    "jobTitle": "[Board-Certified Physician, Professor]",
    "worksFor": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "[Organization Name]",
      "url": "[https://organization.com]"
    },
    "affiliation": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "[Stanford School of Medicine]"
    },
    "alumniOf": {
      "@type": "EducationalOrganization",
      "name": "[Harvard Medical School]"
    },
    "sameAs": [
      "[https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=ABC123]",
      "[https://orcid.org/0000-0001-2345-6789]",
      "[https://linkedin.com/in/author-name]"
    ]
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "[Brand Name]",
    "url": "[https://yourdomain.com]",
    "logo": {
      "@type": "ImageObject",
      "url": "[https://yourdomain.com/logo.png]",
      "width": 600,
      "height": 60
    }
  },
  "mainEntityOfPage": {
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "@id": "[https://yourdomain.com/article-url]"
  },
  "articleSection": "[Category]",
  "keywords": "[primary keyword, semantic keyword, long-tail keyword]",
  "wordCount": 1500,
  "speakable": {
    "@type": "SpeakableSpecification",
    "cssSelector": [".article-summary", ".tldr", "h1", "h2", ".key-takeaways"]
  },
  "about": {
    "@type": "Thing",
    "name": "[Main topic]",
    "description": "[Topic description]"
  },
  "mentions": [
    {
      "@type": "Thing",
      "name": "[Related Entity 1]"
    },
    {
      "@type": "Thing",
      "name": "[Related Entity 2]"
    }
  ],
  "citation": [
    {
      "@type": "CreativeWork",
      "name": "[Study Title]",
      "author": "[Author et al.]",
      "datePublished": "[2024]",
      "url": "[https://pubmed.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/xxxxx]"
    }
  ]
}

/*
USAGE NOTES:

1. E-E-A-T Signals (+40% Citation Boost):
   - honorificSuffix: Add credentials (MD, PhD, MBA, etc.)
   - affiliation: Link to recognized institutions
   - alumniOf: Show educational pedigree
   - sameAs: Link to Google Scholar, ORCID, LinkedIn
   - worksFor: Connect to authoritative organizations

2. Author Schema (Critical):
   - Use full name consistently across site
   - Include all credentials and affiliations
   - Link to external profiles (Google Scholar, ORCID)
   - Create dedicated author bio page
   - Use @id to reference author from multiple articles

3. Dates (Freshness Signals):
   - datePublished: Original publication date
   - dateModified: Last update (update weekly for active content)
   - Use ISO 8601 format (YYYY-MM-DDTHH:MM:SSZ)
   - Perplexity heavily weights recency

4. Speakable (Voice Search):
   - Specify sections for voice assistants to read
   - Include: .tldr, h1, h2, summary sections
   - Keep speakable content concise (29 words)
   - Use natural language phrasing

5. Citations (Credibility):
   - Link to primary sources (PubMed, arXiv)
   - Include study authors and publication year
   - Use DOI or PubMed URL
   - Strengthens E-E-A-T signals

6. Keywords:
   - Use comma-separated list
   - Include primary, semantic, and long-tail
   - Match actual content keywords
   - Don't stuff (5-10 keywords max)

7. Image Requirements:
   - Minimum 1200Ã—630px (Open Graph standard)
   - High quality, compressed
   - Include descriptive caption
   - Alt text in HTML (not schema)

AI PLATFORM OPTIMIZATION:

ChatGPT:
- Prioritizes author credentials
- Values institutional affiliations
- Requires comprehensive coverage (1500+ words)
- Checks citation quality

Perplexity:
- Heavily weights dateModified (update weekly)
- Prefers specialized, deep-dive content
- Values inline citations
- Checks primary source links

Claude:
- Validates credentials through external links
- Requires primary source citations
- Checks institutional affiliations
- Verifies publication dates

Gemini:
- Integrates with Knowledge Graph
- Values traditional authority signals
- Checks Google Scholar profiles
- Prioritizes established entities

EXAMPLE - Medical Article:

{
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  "headline": "Understanding Longevity Biomarkers: A Physician's Guide",
  "datePublished": "2025-01-15T10:00:00Z",
  "dateModified": "2025-11-11T14:30:00Z",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Person",
    "name": "Dr. Sarah Johnson",
    "honorificSuffix": "MD, PhD, FAAD",
    "affiliation": {
      "@type": "Organization",
      "name": "Stanford School of Medicine"
    }
  }
}

PLACEMENT:
Add to <head> or before </body>:
<script type="application/ld+json">
[PASTE JSON HERE]
</script>

TESTING:
- Google Rich Results Test: https://search.google.com/test/rich-results
- Schema Markup Validator: https://validator.schema.org/
- Verify author links resolve correctly
*/
